2026-04-27T19:40:00.4810527Z 13    <!--
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4811033Z 14        Required for reminders to pop as full-screen notifications over the
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4811876Z 15        lock screen when the user enables "Full-Screen Notifications" in
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4813104Z 16        Settings → Notifications. Android 14+ restricts this to apps whose
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4814053Z 17        core function is alarms/calendar/communication; for other apps the
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4815059Z 18        system downgrades it to a heads-up notification, which is fine —
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4815823Z 19        we only request it when the toggle is on.
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4816397Z 20    -->
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4817073Z 21    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.USE_FULL_SCREEN_INTENT" />
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4818498Z 21-->/home/runner/work/prismTask/prismTask/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml:16:5-81
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4819933Z 21-->/home/runner/work/prismTask/prismTask/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml:16:22-78
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4820787Z 22    <!--
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4821407Z 23        Exact alarm permissions. We request both so reminders fire reliably
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4822163Z 24        across Android versions:
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4822887Z 25          - SCHEDULE_EXACT_ALARM: required on Android 12 (API 31-32); the
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4823781Z 26            user must toggle it on via Settings. We prompt for this in
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4824671Z 27            MainActivity when canScheduleExactAlarms() returns false.
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4825573Z 28          - USE_EXACT_ALARM: auto-granted on Android 13+ (API 33+) for
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4826478Z 29            calendar/reminder/timer-style apps, so no prompt is needed.
2026-04-27T19:40:00.4827377Z 30        Without USE_EXACT_ALARM the app was silently falling back to
